<subSubSection id="6EC73BF27A29D9E8648672EFA3A33AAF" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="6E954C314361D2162CFE81BEF52925C5" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="7C6D11FD37A71DDC2B86C4026A2BB310" LSID="795F8D5A-70C9-5ACC-8E72-FDD94D4DE30A" authority="Zamani, Chatzaki, Esyunin &amp; Marusik, 2021" authorityName="Zamani, Chatzaki, Esyunin &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2021" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Zagrotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zagrotes" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Zagrotes Zamani, Chatzaki, Esyunin &amp; Marusik, 2021</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="611BE49F3A0F39E870B2925DC797FB66" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" type="comments">
<paragraph id="DD40FC1AF7012955955C5B922C89C206" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5EDC4D7DF8AEA4D805C7F54C4E30EB40" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">
This genus was recently described as monotypic from southwestern and southern Iran, with 
<taxonomicName id="CCC9EE1D7F5A65A47CCEF82CAD6151C5" authority="Zamani, Chatzaki, Esyunin &amp; Marusik, 2021" authorityName="Zamani, Chatzaki, Esyunin &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2021" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Zagrotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zagrotes apophysalis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apophysalis">
<emphasis id="6830406499D7BBBE87C4455784E6E964" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Zagrotes apophysalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Zamani, Chatzaki, Esyunin &amp; Marusik, 2021 as the type species. In the same paper, 
<bibRefCitation id="F25EBADA9E8932494D8334A1DE39B4E5" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5852/ejt.2021.751.1381" author="Zamani, A" journalOrPublisher="European Journal of Taxonomy" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" pagination="68 - 114" refId="B15" refString="Zamani, A, Chatzaki, M, Esyunin, SL, Marusik, YM, 2021a. One new genus and nineteen new species of ground spiders (Araneae: Gnaphosidae) from Iran, with other taxonomic considerations. European Journal of Taxonomy 751: 68 - 114, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5852/ejt.2021.751.1381" title="One new genus and nineteen new species of ground spiders (Araneae: Gnaphosidae) from Iran, with other taxonomic considerations." url="https://doi.org/10.5852/ejt.2021.751.1381" volume="751" year="2021 a">Zamani et al. (2021a)</bibRefCitation>
described another similar species in another genus, namely 
<taxonomicName id="D39F1A9781F2A2B6D17029427446D963" authorityName="Zamani, Chatzaki, Esyunin &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2021" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berinda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Berinda bifurcata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifurcata">
<emphasis id="ABE490EC9B33C5FEFF87C949D3FA6BCC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Berinda bifurcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Zamani, Chatzaki, Esyunin &amp; Marusik, 2021. The two new species described here are closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="5234C03FC95FBC2B3958BD73CEE992CC" genus="B." lsidName="B. bifurcata" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" rank="species" species="bifurcata">
<emphasis id="D9796940932D4E12143F4E5D70805766" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">B. bifurcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and to a lesser degree to 
<taxonomicName id="85A4147C34DCCC8CD2AEA5D622A8FF22" genus="Z." lsidName="Z. apophysalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" rank="species" species="apophysalis">
<emphasis id="10B41C8D2A6AE60E9E7F5B13D444A841" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Z. apophysalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. All species possess a bifurcated RTA and similar conformation of the bulb. For this reason, we propose a new combination, 
<taxonomicName id="C58CF2EA623C5111752B242C14B89BD1" authority="Zamani, Chatzaki, Esyunin &amp; Marusik, 2021" authorityName="Zamani, Chatzaki, Esyunin &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2021" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Zagrotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zagrotes bifurcatus" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifurcatus">
<emphasis id="A13EFFE15E81D6CCA9EFC7888E58BB91" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Zagrotes bifurcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Zamani, Chatzaki, Esyunin &amp; Marusik, 2021), comb. nov., despite the fact that this species and the two new ones described here lack modifications on palpal patella and swollen tibia that are present in the type species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="58964F30A16FAE7A4F558ABB1A1504D4" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" type="composition">
<paragraph id="ACFBA98AA2B41F52F6A50FDF53416022" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Composition.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4622E39965DB762D6741516327CEDB5B" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">
Four species: 
<taxonomicName id="206B75A950791E389E89F6069AA8E390" genus="Z." lsidName="Z. apophysalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" rank="species" species="apophysalis">
<emphasis id="81353C28994F41F9DE3FD749538531F0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Z. apophysalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D1F4E705E81C50BE0D749186239C8216" genus="Z." lsidName="Z. borna" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" rank="species" species="borna">
<emphasis id="9B6C616883A1EC86ADC8C3BE8FF1C900" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Z. borna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., 
<taxonomicName id="BE4C09DD74F239F8EC0719960E623D48" genus="Z." lsidName="Z. bifurcatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" rank="species" species="bifurcatus">
<emphasis id="E5FE732977F9D5BC553808D1E9EE5257" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Z. bifurcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov., and 
<taxonomicName id="6BCCB2FAC1A25FAF5D351D3BDCDA1555" genus="Z." lsidName="Z. parla" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" rank="species" species="parla">
<emphasis id="AFC008DA60C778B001946DE4D73F2671" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Z. parla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="868D28C0DDFA9D2FDDE90284BD865892" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0865B1A6C1C49B2654EFBD9A28E2A77F" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B9D4B3206FDB9C942B20B00AAC6907D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Endemic to Iran, distributed along the southwestern and southern slopes of Zagros Mountains, from Kohgiluyeh and Boyer-Ahmad to Hormozgan.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
